diff:1670642263:1670464620:=88,105d87%0a%3c #foxbegin 221210-031743-603800#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Interesting factoids about Manchu grammar %0a%3c -> - tiagocecchi1216%0a%3c -> [-09.12.2022 - 19:17-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221210-031743-603800 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c Manchu has many interesting linguistic features. One particularly unique feature of Manchu is its ‘vowel harmony’ in accordance with classical philosophy found in the I Ching. Generally, vowels are divided into two categories; yin, or femenine objects are categorized by front vowels, and yang, or masculine objects that are categorized by back vowels. That is, changing the vowel of a word also changes its gender.%0a%3c %0a%3c Despite how endangered the language is, its historical importance means it has made a profound linguistic impact on Mandarin in the form of a great many loan words. In fact, this relationship is reciprocal, with many words in Manchu themselves loan words from Mandarin.%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221210-031743-603800#%0a
