diff:1670464620:1670430275:=71,87d70%0a%3c #foxbegin 221208-015700-539410#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Reasons that Manchu language becomes endangered %0a%3c -> - tingchen%0a%3c -> [-07.12.2022 - 17:57-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221208-015700-539410 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c There are several historical factors that prevent Manchus to spread their language in 1800s when they were ruling over China. First, the Manchu itself was not a complete system and the lack of documentation made it hard to spread. Second, the population of Manchu people, especially the ones who can actually speak Manchu language, was too small compared to Han people. It is impossible for them to teach all the Han people their language verbally, without any documentation of their language, and within 300 years. Finally, for Manchu people, if they want to rule over the whole Han population, the fastest way is to use Han language. Therefore, they voluntarily “abandoned” Manchu language and it makes this language endangered nowadays.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221208-015700-539410#%0a
